# {{.ProjectName}}

> Built with the **GOTH** stack: **G**o · **templ** · **HTMX** · **Tailwind**

## Quick start

```bash
cp .env.example .env   # fill in your values
make setup             # initial build, install tools, download JS assets
make dev               # start live-reload dev server
```

## Environment variables

| Variable | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `PORT` | `3090` | HTTP listen port |
| `DB_PATH` | `./internal/data/database.db` | SQLite database path |
| `APP_ENV` | *(unset)* | Set to `production` for production mode |

## Make targets

### Development

```bash
make setup        # install templ, air, tailwind, download HTMX + Alpine
make dev          # live reload (air + templ watcher + tailwind watcher)
make build-mac    # compile production binary for macOS
make build-pi     # cross-compile production binary for linux/arm64
make clean        # remove temp files, binary, and generated templ code
```

### Database

```bash
make backup       # timestamped backup → backups/
make restore      # interactively restore a backup
make db-optimize  # VACUUM & ANALYZE the local database
make db-shell     # open SQLite shell with pretty-printing
```

### Pi / VPS deploy

Pi deploy targets are provided by `makefiles/pi.mk`. To enable:

1. Uncomment `include makefiles/pi.mk` in the `Makefile`
2. Add the following to your `.env`:

```bash
PI=pi             # SSH alias from ~/.ssh/config
```

Available targets:

```bash
make setup-pi          # prepare Pi directories and install sqlite3_rsync
make setup-service     # install / update the systemd service on the Pi
make deploy            # build for Pi and rsync binary to production
make status            # service status, DB size, disk usage, recent logs
make logs              # tail the remote app log in real-time
make clear-logs        # truncate the remote log file
make db-push           # push local database to Pi (confirms before overwrite)
make db-pull           # pull Pi database locally (saved as *.debug.db)
make db-optimize-remote # VACUUM & ANALYZE the Pi database
make db-shell-remote   # open SQLite shell on the Pi database
make bench             # 500MB sequential write benchmark on Pi NVMe
make pi-reboot         # gracefully stop app, sync filesystem, reboot Pi
```

